1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,520
If you don't want to
be like everyone else,

2
00:00:02,520 --> 00:00:06,030
broke, stressed, and stuck
in a never ending cycle,

3
00:00:06,030 --> 00:00:08,460
you need to focus on one thing:

4
00:00:08,460 --> 00:00:11,820
making your first $10,000.

5
00:00:11,820 --> 00:00:15,630
When I was 18, I had no
money and no qualifications,

6
00:00:15,630 --> 00:00:17,940
but I did have big ambitions.

7
00:00:17,940 --> 00:00:20,310
Instead of worrying about making millions,

8
00:00:20,310 --> 00:00:22,110
I set myself the smaller,

9
00:00:22,110 --> 00:00:24,720
more achievable goal of making 10K.

10
00:00:24,720 --> 00:00:26,850
Now, as a self-made millionaire,

11
00:00:26,850 --> 00:00:29,790
I can tell you that first $10,000

12
00:00:29,790 --> 00:00:31,500
was the hardest to make.

13
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:34,080
But once I hit it, everything changed.

14
00:00:34,080 --> 00:00:35,910
It wasn't just about the money.

15
00:00:35,910 --> 00:00:37,740
It was about proving to myself

16
00:00:37,740 --> 00:00:40,440
that making money is a skill and not luck.

17
00:00:40,440 --> 00:00:42,870
Once I figured out how to make 10K once,

18
00:00:42,870 --> 00:00:45,360
I knew I could do it again and again

19
00:00:45,360 --> 00:00:48,060
and eventually scale it into real well.

20
00:00:48,060 --> 00:00:50,130
So if I had to start from zero

21
00:00:50,130 --> 00:00:53,370
and make that first
$10,000 all over again,

22
00:00:53,370 --> 00:00:56,537
this is exactly how I
do it in three steps.

23
00:00:56,537 --> 00:00:59,130
(slow upbeat music)

24
00:00:59,130 --> 00:01:02,490
Most people make this way
harder than it needs to be.

25
00:01:02,490 --> 00:01:03,750
They jump into crypto

26
00:01:03,750 --> 00:01:05,580
because their friend made money from it,

27
00:01:05,580 --> 00:01:07,320
or they tried day trading

28
00:01:07,320 --> 00:01:10,050
because some guru promised
it would make them rich.

29
00:01:10,050 --> 00:01:12,000
The problem is both these methods

30
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:15,300
need huge upfront cash
reserves and crazy luck.

31
00:01:15,300 --> 00:01:16,527
These are side hustles

32
00:01:16,527 --> 00:01:19,770
and they should never be seen
as your main source of income.

33
00:01:19,770 --> 00:01:23,310
Instead, think of them as
tools to multiply your money.

34
00:01:23,310 --> 00:01:24,570
When you are just starting out,

35
00:01:24,570 --> 00:01:25,980
you need something that requires

36
00:01:25,980 --> 00:01:28,050
a small amount of money to begin with

37
00:01:28,050 --> 00:01:30,810
and constantly puts cash
in your pocket every day.

38
00:01:30,810 --> 00:01:32,700
When you strip away all the noise,

39
00:01:32,700 --> 00:01:34,860
there are only really four options.

40
00:01:34,860 --> 00:01:36,120
I've tried all of these,

41
00:01:36,120 --> 00:01:37,410
and take it from me,

42
00:01:37,410 --> 00:01:39,090
this choice is crucial

43
00:01:39,090 --> 00:01:41,940
because some options
offer higher scalability

44
00:01:41,940 --> 00:01:43,920
while others are more limited.

45
00:01:43,920 --> 00:01:44,940
In the same way,

46
00:01:44,940 --> 00:01:46,590
some generate quick cash

47
00:01:46,590 --> 00:01:48,900
while others take more time to make money.

48
00:01:48,900 --> 00:01:51,338
Option one is selling in-person services.

49
00:01:51,338 --> 00:01:53,460
Look, you've probably
heard of these before,

50
00:01:53,460 --> 00:01:55,800
but I'm talking personal training,

51
00:01:55,800 --> 00:01:57,535
delivery driving, dog walking,

52
00:01:57,535 --> 00:02:00,864
nail designing, barbering, videography,

53
00:02:00,864 --> 00:02:02,670
and so many more.

54
00:02:02,670 --> 00:02:05,370
Although these services
sound so common and basic,

55
00:02:05,370 --> 00:02:08,550
they're actually one of the
fastest ways to make money,

56
00:02:08,550 --> 00:02:11,280
so don't overlook them
as they give you a way

57
00:02:11,280 --> 00:02:13,050
to get paid immediately.

58
00:02:13,050 --> 00:02:15,450
It's also pretty cheap to get started.

59
00:02:15,450 --> 00:02:18,540
All you need is some skills
and maybe a few tools,

60
00:02:18,540 --> 00:02:21,300
which means you can get up
and running very quickly.

61
00:02:21,300 --> 00:02:22,770
If you choose to do this,

62
00:02:22,770 --> 00:02:25,650
then please don't mess around
trying to build a website,

63
00:02:25,650 --> 00:02:27,810
run ads, or make a logo.

64
00:02:27,810 --> 00:02:29,010
Just get out there.

65
00:02:29,010 --> 00:02:31,290
Find some customers in your local area.

66
00:02:31,290 --> 00:02:33,990
Deliver the service and get paid.

67
00:02:33,990 --> 00:02:36,420
I even did this when I was in my teens.

68
00:02:36,420 --> 00:02:38,460
I used to walk around rich neighborhoods

69
00:02:38,460 --> 00:02:40,440
and offer to wash people's cars.

70
00:02:40,440 --> 00:02:44,040
I'd look out for tidy
gardens but dirty vehicles.

71
00:02:44,040 --> 00:02:45,930
Now, this might sound strange.

72
00:02:45,930 --> 00:02:48,360
However, I was betting
if they were obsessed

73
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:50,100
over keeping their garden tidy,

74
00:02:50,100 --> 00:02:52,710
they'd also want a nice
shiny car on their driveway

75
00:02:52,710 --> 00:02:54,060
to impress their neighbors.

76
00:02:54,060 --> 00:02:55,650
Because these kinds of services

77
00:02:55,650 --> 00:02:57,480
are limited by your local area,

78
00:02:57,480 --> 00:02:59,910
it meant my demand was pretty up and down.

79
00:02:59,910 --> 00:03:01,320
Some months were busy

80
00:03:01,320 --> 00:03:04,020
and others I struggled to make anything.

81
00:03:04,020 --> 00:03:05,280
When I was busy,

82
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:07,566
I was only able to work
with one person at a time,

83
00:03:07,566 --> 00:03:09,808
which kept how much I could make in a day.

84
00:03:09,808 --> 00:03:13,650
So in-person services are
great to get started with,

85
00:03:13,650 --> 00:03:15,240
but you can quickly feel

86
00:03:15,240 --> 00:03:17,430
like they're limiting your potential.

87
00:03:17,430 --> 00:03:19,603
That brings me onto option two,

88
00:03:19,603 --> 00:03:21,840
which is local products.

89
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:22,890
This is selling things

90
00:03:22,890 --> 00:03:25,620
like home baked goods, handmade items,

91
00:03:25,620 --> 00:03:27,510
artwork, fresh produce,

92
00:03:27,510 --> 00:03:28,500
and much more.

93
00:03:28,500 --> 00:03:30,420
This can be a great way to make money,

94
00:03:30,420 --> 00:03:33,210
but it's not something
that happens overnight.

95
00:03:33,210 --> 00:03:34,980
Unlike services where you get paid

96
00:03:34,980 --> 00:03:36,450
as soon as the job's done,

97
00:03:36,450 --> 00:03:38,490
selling local products takes time.

98
00:03:38,490 --> 00:03:40,620
I gave this a go using some of the profits

99
00:03:40,620 --> 00:03:42,360
from my car washing business.

100
00:03:42,360 --> 00:03:44,580
I bought some cheap model playing parts,

101
00:03:44,580 --> 00:03:46,830
then spent some time building each one up,

102
00:03:46,830 --> 00:03:49,560
and then sold them to people
at the RC Flying Club,

103
00:03:49,560 --> 00:03:51,270
which I went to on the weekends.

104
00:03:51,270 --> 00:03:53,580
However, I quickly realized

105
00:03:53,580 --> 00:03:56,820
I was putting a lot of work
in for very little money.

106
00:03:56,820 --> 00:03:58,860
This was hard for me to come to terms with

107
00:03:58,860 --> 00:04:00,960
because I really enjoyed building them.

108
00:04:00,960 --> 00:04:03,060
Most of my earnings were being eaten up

109
00:04:03,060 --> 00:04:04,770
by the cost of materials.

110
00:04:04,770 --> 00:04:05,820
And on top of that,

111
00:04:05,820 --> 00:04:08,310
my customer base was very limited

112
00:04:08,310 --> 00:04:10,920
as there weren't enough people
willing to pay what I needed

113
00:04:10,920 --> 00:04:12,300
to make it worth my time.

114
00:04:12,300 --> 00:04:14,271
So selling local products can be fun

115
00:04:14,271 --> 00:04:16,020
and it's definitely worth it

116
00:04:16,020 --> 00:04:18,300
if you wanna make some money
from something you love.

117
00:04:18,300 --> 00:04:21,210
Option three is global products.

118
00:04:21,210 --> 00:04:23,430
This includes starting a clothing brand,

119
00:04:23,430 --> 00:04:25,830
drop shipping, sneaker reselling,

120
00:04:25,830 --> 00:04:27,668
print on-demand, and so much more.

121
00:04:27,668 --> 00:04:31,260
Unlike in-person services
or local products,

122
00:04:31,260 --> 00:04:33,060
going global means you have access

123
00:04:33,060 --> 00:04:34,890
to a much larger customer base,

124
00:04:34,890 --> 00:04:37,740
which gives you more
opportunities to make money.

125
00:04:37,740 --> 00:04:41,010
You are not limited to just the
people in your town or city,

126
00:04:41,010 --> 00:04:43,590
anyone anywhere can buy from you.

127
00:04:43,590 --> 00:04:47,190
I was so excited about launching
my own global products.

128
00:04:47,190 --> 00:04:49,320
I even flew all the way to China

129
00:04:49,320 --> 00:04:51,060
to partner with a manufacturer

130
00:04:51,060 --> 00:04:53,040
to produce my model airplane designs

131
00:04:53,040 --> 00:04:54,510
and sell them worldwide.

132
00:04:54,510 --> 00:04:56,430
Of course, you don't have to do this

133
00:04:56,430 --> 00:04:58,290
if you choose to go down the drop shipping

134
00:04:58,290 --> 00:04:59,970
or print on-demand routes.

135
00:04:59,970 --> 00:05:02,820
However, this wasn't really
an option when I started.

136
00:05:02,820 --> 00:05:05,940
If I'm honest, things started
off pretty slowly for me

137
00:05:05,940 --> 00:05:08,100
because I had to keep
reinvesting my profits

138
00:05:08,100 --> 00:05:09,930
back into new products to sell.

139
00:05:09,930 --> 00:05:12,540
Every sale required more investment.

140
00:05:12,540 --> 00:05:14,070
Once I sold 10 items,

141
00:05:14,070 --> 00:05:16,500
I then needed to buy 20 more to keep up.

142
00:05:16,500 --> 00:05:18,240
Instead of pocketing the profits,

143
00:05:18,240 --> 00:05:19,680
my money kept getting trapped

144
00:05:19,680 --> 00:05:22,110
in this endless cycle of restocking.

145
00:05:22,110 --> 00:05:25,800
Ultimately, was it worth it? 100%.

146
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:27,750
However, you should only do this

147
00:05:27,750 --> 00:05:30,120
if you have the patience
to wait one to three months

148
00:05:30,120 --> 00:05:32,010
for everything to start kicking off.

149
00:05:32,010 --> 00:05:33,840
So when this is up and running,

150
00:05:33,840 --> 00:05:36,870
it is probably the most
passive laziest way

151
00:05:36,870 --> 00:05:38,550
to make money that actually works.

152
00:05:38,550 --> 00:05:41,850
So that brings us onto option four,

153
00:05:41,850 --> 00:05:43,950
selling online services.

154
00:05:43,950 --> 00:05:46,080
This option wasn't
actually possible for me

155
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:47,040
when I was younger,

156
00:05:47,040 --> 00:05:49,470
but this is such an advantage nowadays.

157
00:05:49,470 --> 00:05:52,440
There are so many different
online services you can offer.

158
00:05:52,440 --> 00:05:55,440
These include copywriting, video editing,

159
00:05:55,440 --> 00:05:57,360
thumbnail design, running ads,

160
00:05:57,360 --> 00:05:59,010
social media management,

161
00:05:59,010 --> 00:06:00,390
the list goes on.

162
00:06:00,390 --> 00:06:02,820
Selling online services actually combines

163
00:06:02,820 --> 00:06:06,390
the two biggest benefits
from the in-person services

164
00:06:06,390 --> 00:06:08,040
and global products.

165
00:06:08,040 --> 00:06:10,140
This is because you get the global reach,

166
00:06:10,140 --> 00:06:12,090
but the profit margins of a service.

167
00:06:12,090 --> 00:06:15,330
With products, you might
make 20 to 30% margin

168
00:06:15,330 --> 00:06:17,310
that needs to be reinvested.

169
00:06:17,310 --> 00:06:20,616
With services, you are
looking at 70 to 80% margins

170
00:06:20,616 --> 00:06:22,980
that go straight into your pocket,

171
00:06:22,980 --> 00:06:25,530
plus you can start making
money from day one.

172
00:06:25,530 --> 00:06:27,900
Look, all of these are fantastic ways

173
00:06:27,900 --> 00:06:30,240
to make $10,000 as a student,

174
00:06:30,240 --> 00:06:32,970
especially these last two options.

175
00:06:32,970 --> 00:06:35,400
However, if I wanted to start making money

176
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:36,840
as fast as possible,

177
00:06:36,840 --> 00:06:38,910
then I'd go with option four:

178
00:06:38,910 --> 00:06:41,760
selling online services.

179
00:06:41,760 --> 00:06:43,920
So now we need to figure out exactly

180
00:06:43,920 --> 00:06:45,872
what online service to offer.

181
00:06:45,872 --> 00:06:49,800
So start by asking
yourself three questions.

182
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:51,660
What are you really good at?

183
00:06:51,660 --> 00:06:53,400
What do you enjoy learning about?

184
00:06:53,400 --> 00:06:56,970
And what problems do businesses
consistently struggle with?

185
00:06:56,970 --> 00:06:59,520
The sweet spot is where
your answers overlap.

186
00:06:59,520 --> 00:07:01,500
Most people get stuck at this stage

187
00:07:01,500 --> 00:07:03,330
as they spend months or even years

188
00:07:03,330 --> 00:07:06,600
trying to perfect their skill
before offering it to anyone.

189
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:08,370
That is totally backwards.

190
00:07:08,370 --> 00:07:10,680
You need to start getting
real-world experience

191
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:12,450
as quickly as possible.

192
00:07:12,450 --> 00:07:14,130
So start by setting your prices

193
00:07:14,130 --> 00:07:16,050
under the normal market rate.

194
00:07:16,050 --> 00:07:18,699
Your main aim here is to earn
and learn at the same time.

195
00:07:18,699 --> 00:07:21,479
Now, let's take this one step further.

196
00:07:21,479 --> 00:07:24,150
(slow upbeat music)

197
00:07:24,150 --> 00:07:28,410
This is the skill pyramid
made up of four elements

198
00:07:28,410 --> 00:07:30,090
that when mastered together,

199
00:07:30,090 --> 00:07:32,100
transform a high income skill

200
00:07:32,100 --> 00:07:34,560
into a $10,000 income.

201
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:37,500
Miss just one and you'll
stay stuck at the bottom,

202
00:07:37,500 --> 00:07:39,831
working hard but never breaking through.

203
00:07:39,831 --> 00:07:42,930
Element one is positioning.

204
00:07:42,930 --> 00:07:45,900
You see, not all online
services are equal.

205
00:07:45,900 --> 00:07:48,720
The real money is in
offering to help businesses

206
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:49,740
make more money.

207
00:07:49,740 --> 00:07:51,960
That's because businesses
think about money

208
00:07:51,960 --> 00:07:53,640
differently to individuals.

209
00:07:53,640 --> 00:07:56,580
When a business is making $50,000 a month,

210
00:07:56,580 --> 00:08:00,420
spending 2,000 to solve a
problem isn't a big deal

211
00:08:00,420 --> 00:08:02,580
as long as it helps 'em make more money.

212
00:08:02,580 --> 00:08:03,870
And take it from me,

213
00:08:03,870 --> 00:08:05,760
they have a lot of these problems.

214
00:08:05,760 --> 00:08:07,380
They need more customers.

215
00:08:07,380 --> 00:08:08,820
They need better systems.

216
00:08:08,820 --> 00:08:11,010
They need to stand out
from their competition.

217
00:08:11,010 --> 00:08:13,920
And they need to convert
more leads into sales.

218
00:08:13,920 --> 00:08:16,200
These problems never go away

219
00:08:16,200 --> 00:08:19,200
and businesses are always
willing to pay to solve them.

220
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:20,370
On top of this,

221
00:08:20,370 --> 00:08:23,580
some industries simply have
more money to spend than others.

222
00:08:23,580 --> 00:08:26,280
And if you think about how
you can reposition yourself,

223
00:08:26,280 --> 00:08:28,890
you'll start making real money faster.

224
00:08:28,890 --> 00:08:31,110
Here are some ideas to get you thinking.

225
00:08:31,110 --> 00:08:34,230
Instead of being a video
editor for small YouTubers,

226
00:08:34,230 --> 00:08:36,300
you could edit videos for an entrepreneur

227
00:08:36,300 --> 00:08:37,650
who sells a product.

228
00:08:37,650 --> 00:08:40,080
If you make random thumbnails for clients,

229
00:08:40,080 --> 00:08:43,020
you could instead aim to
become the main designer

230
00:08:43,020 --> 00:08:44,910
for an established creator.

231
00:08:44,910 --> 00:08:46,470
And if you're a copywriter,

232
00:08:46,470 --> 00:08:48,090
don't write cheap articles.

233
00:08:48,090 --> 00:08:50,976
Instead, focus on
optimizing landing pages.

234
00:08:50,976 --> 00:08:53,370
This isn't about learning more skills,

235
00:08:53,370 --> 00:08:56,070
it's about putting yourself
where the money's being made.

236
00:08:56,070 --> 00:08:58,170
Element two is leverage.

237
00:08:58,170 --> 00:08:59,940
You'll never make $10,000

238
00:08:59,940 --> 00:09:02,550
without leveraging value over time.

239
00:09:02,550 --> 00:09:04,920
Businesses don't pay for effort.

240
00:09:04,920 --> 00:09:06,330
They pay for results.

241
00:09:06,330 --> 00:09:08,490
If you stop charging
for the hours you work

242
00:09:08,490 --> 00:09:11,730
and instead for the return
on investment you provide,

243
00:09:11,730 --> 00:09:13,770
you'll instantly make more money.

244
00:09:13,770 --> 00:09:16,290
Let's say you choose to run Facebook ads.

245
00:09:16,290 --> 00:09:17,730
If you charge per hour,

246
00:09:17,730 --> 00:09:19,860
you are stuck with a fixed rate

247
00:09:19,860 --> 00:09:22,470
and the client will always
want to keep your hours low.

248
00:09:22,470 --> 00:09:24,060
But if you charge based on the money

249
00:09:24,060 --> 00:09:25,800
you bring in for the business,

250
00:09:25,800 --> 00:09:28,380
suddenly they're not thinking about cost,

251
00:09:28,380 --> 00:09:30,240
they're thinking about profit.

252
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:31,620
And when they see that your work

253
00:09:31,620 --> 00:09:33,300
is directly making them money,

254
00:09:33,300 --> 00:09:35,040
they'll happily pay you more for it.

255
00:09:35,040 --> 00:09:36,480
The same goes for if you decide

256
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:38,370
to offer social media management.

257
00:09:38,370 --> 00:09:40,920
If you just schedule posts
and reply to comments,

258
00:09:40,920 --> 00:09:42,300
you are replaceable.

259
00:09:42,300 --> 00:09:44,310
But if you can prove that your strategy

260
00:09:44,310 --> 00:09:46,320
is bringing in more engagement,

261
00:09:46,320 --> 00:09:48,540
more leads and more sales,

262
00:09:48,540 --> 00:09:51,660
you become a valuable
asset, not just an expense.

263
00:09:51,660 --> 00:09:53,910
Trust me, the moment you shift your pitch

264
00:09:53,910 --> 00:09:55,740
from what you do to what they gain,

265
00:09:55,740 --> 00:09:56,850
you'll find a lot of people

266
00:09:56,850 --> 00:09:58,530
are suddenly willing to pay a lot more.

267
00:09:58,530 --> 00:10:00,431
Element three is reach.

268
00:10:00,431 --> 00:10:03,690
One of the biggest mistakes
people make when starting out

269
00:10:03,690 --> 00:10:06,390
is thinking they always
have to chase clients,

270
00:10:06,390 --> 00:10:09,240
